# mgc_container_registry_proxy_cache (Data Source)

Retrieves information about a specific proxy cache.

## Example Usage

```terraform
data "mgc_container_registry_proxy_cache" "proxy_cache" {
  id = "proxy-cache-id"
}

output "proxy_cache" {
  value = {
    id            = data.mgc_container_registry_proxy_cache.proxy_cache.id
    name          = data.mgc_container_registry_proxy_cache.proxy_cache.name
    description   = data.mgc_container_registry_proxy_cache.proxy_cache.description
    provider_name = data.mgc_container_registry_proxy_cache.proxy_cache.provider_name
    url           = data.mgc_container_registry_proxy_cache.proxy_cache.url
    created_at    = data.mgc_container_registry_proxy_cache.proxy_cache.created_at
    updated_at    = data.mgc_container_registry_proxy_cache.proxy_cache.updated_at
  }
}
```

<!-- schema generated by tfplugindocs -->
## Schema

### Required

- `id` (String) Unique identifier for the proxy cache

### Read-Only

- `created_at` (String) The timestamp when the proxy cache was created
- `description` (String) Description of the proxy cache
- `name` (String) Unique name for each tenant, used for the proxy cache
- `provider_name` (String) Provider identifier
- `updated_at` (String) The timestamp when the proxy cache was last updated
- `url` (String) Endpoint URL for the proxied registry
